              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">March 18, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 2645</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly<font color="#B30000"><strike> Member</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Members</i></font> Jeff Gonzalez<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> and Tangipa</i></font><br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 20, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to add Article 3 (commencing with Section 983) to Chapter 6 of Division 4 of the Military and Veterans Code, relating to veterans.</span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 2645, as amended, Jeff Gonzalez.
                          Veterans: registration and identification services.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law establishes the Department of Veterans Affairs, which administers various programs that provide benefits to veterans, as<font color="#B30000"><strike> defined, including educational assistance and farm and home purchase assistance.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> defined. Existing law additionally establishes a statewide system of veterans’ homes to provide room, board, and other services to eligible veterans and their spouses or domestic partners.</i></font></div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law establishes the Department of Motor Vehicles in the Transportation Agency and sets forth various powers and duties for the department, including prescribing and providing suitable forms of applications, certificates of ownership, registration
			 cards, driver’s licenses, and all other forms that are deemed necessary.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would require the Department of Motor Vehicles, in coordination with the Department of Veterans Affairs, to provide mobile services to each<font color="#B30000"><strike> veteran</strike></font> resident at each California<font color="#B30000"><strike> veterans</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> veterans</i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>’</i></font> home at least once per calendar year. The bill would require the Department of Veterans Affairs to assist by coordinating the scheduling, space, and outreach to residents to facilitate the provision of those services. For the purposes of these provisions, the bill would define “mobile services” as, among other
			 things,<font color="#B30000"><strike> vehicle registration services</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> issuance or renewal of driver’s licenses and identification</i></font> and Real ID application processing.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.7166646941989792"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Article 3 (commencing with Section 983) is added to Chapter 6 of Division 4 of the Military and Veterans Code, to read:</div><div><div><div id="id_A7842D21-FA73-4C4F-A92D-E19CFE29F575"><div><h5 style="text-align:left;">
                Article
               3. Department of Motor Vehicles Mobile Services for Veterans</h5></div></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">983.</h6> (a) (1) The Department of Motor Vehicles shall coordinate with the Department of Veterans Affairs to provide mobile services at each California<font color="#B30000"><strike> veterans</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> veterans</i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>’</i></font> home at least one time per calendar year.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) The Department of Veterans Affairs shall assist in coordinating the scheduling, space, and outreach to residents to facilitate the provision of services described in this section.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) Mobile services provided pursuant to this section shall be made available to any<font color="#B30000"><strike> veteran that is a</strike></font> resident of a<font color="#B30000"><strike> veterans</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> veterans</i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>’</i></font> home.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) Mobile services provided pursuant to this section may include, but are not limited to,<font color="#B30000"><strike> all</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> both</i></font> of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Issuance or renewal of driver’s licenses and identification cards.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(2)<span class="EnSpace"/>Vehicle registration services.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(3)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2)</i></font> Real ID application processing.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(d) This section does not preclude the Department of Motor Vehicles from providing additional visits or services at a<font color="#B30000"><strike> veterans</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						  veterans</i></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>’</i></font> home when feasible.</div></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
